The paper deals with the recognition of circle graphs, which are a subclass of intersection graphs. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a likely category. The paper also presents a new data structure and algorithm for circle graphs, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions Split Decomposition, which is a graph decomposition technique, indicating that it could belong to cs.GT (Graph Theory). Finally, the paper deals with practical and efficient algorithms, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
